Imbued with excess and pain, the imagination of the dark mechanics forged the Sirenbow class Stalker.
Walking guns, they stalk across the battlefield picking off targets before they know it.

This kit includes everything you need to build a Sirenbow Stalkers in 8mm or AT scale.
The main body measures about the height of the standard Stalker.
This can be built in any number of ways, the kit is flexible with the legs and body being posable.

The kit includes, amongst standard components:
- 2 different feet
- 3 tail weapon options

Four files include:
1. Supported: individual components to print and pose as you desire.
2. Unsupported: as above but supported.
3. Complete: some example builds which you can use as an example or print as a single object. Supported versions included.

The model has been made to go on a 50mm bases and this has been included.


All files come supported and unsupported.

Pictures of models are test prints.
Pictured in the background are the [Rapture Heavy Stalkers](https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/rapture-heavy-stalkers-8mm)

Hunters of titans, they bound and leap across the battlefield after their prey.

This kit includes everything you need to build a Rapture Heavy Stalker in 8mm or AT scale.
The main body measures about the height of the standard Heavy Stalker with the tail adding extra height.
This can be built in any number of ways, the kit is extremely flexible.

The kit includes, amongst standard components:
- 3 different heads, with and without tentacles
- 2 tail poses
- 2 different tail weapons
- 2 different arm weapons

Four files include:
1. Components: individual components to print and pose as you desire. Includes the supported folder.

A free upgrade kit for your smaller knight models, released along with the Project Abby conversion kit found here...

https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/project-abby-conversion-kit-for-naughty-knights

Included in this kit are...

-FOUR nasty blades, including three chain weapons and a cleaner-looking power weapon.

-FIVE claws, including a pincer with dual saws.

-Three triple-missile launchers in vertical, horizontal, and triangular configurations. Two poses are offered: straight ahead, and tilted back for launch.

-UPDATE: The missile launchers were a little big for my taste, so I have included 12 new files (supported and clean) for launchers reduced about 15%. Either can be used. Also, if you're using the mounting peg, some sanding/filing may be necessary, especially after paint.

-Three main weapon bodies, with three degrees of tilt.

-Two forearm weapons extensions.

-Five Suturus Pattern upper arms at various fixed angles. The upper arms twist-lock to fit with factory kits.

Note: This upgrade kit requires a small amount of hobby time and effort.
I recommend you magnetize the upper arms at the elbow flat with a 8mm-wide diameter x 3mm- or 2mm-thick magnet.
I would then glue steel washers to the top of the main weapon body.

Thanks!

Best, JBR

Please use these files and their resulting prints for private use only, unless you have secured a production license. Gracias.

Supported and Clean versions of all files are in the zipped folders.

All .stl files optimized for printing on resin 3d printers.

Demon hordes for warmaster both with and without supports using Duncan Shadow's awesome demons.

10mm demon army
See my collections for the other units; I have a unit for each of the roles in warmaster revolution and a couple of heroes. Note that this army does not inherently match one of the big four chaos gods by design, as I find them dreadfully boring.

Supports
The supports are auto generated by Prusa. The strips are densely supported, but I haven't had any failures. The worst that's happened is me breaking off an arm of one of the demons on the edges of the strip when impatiently clipping through the supports.

Why?
I just got a 3d printer and was looking to get into warmaster with some friends when I noticed that there is no ready to print demon army yet. Given my 0-level modelling skills I instead decided to use existing models to create the army; this unit is one of the outcomes of this project.

Disclaimer
To be sure: none of these models are actually mine. I am a complete hack blundering his way through blender; all I can do is resize models, fatten segments and add cylinders (you may spot some of my handiwork on other models).
